GLOBAL CONTEXT — Read before every single response.

PROJECT: ShieldSentinel — Professional Security Assessment Platform
MACHINE: Mac M2 (Apple Silicon) — cloud scalable later
DEVELOPER: Full stack, beginner to security tooling

ARCHITECTURE PHILOSOPHY:
- Clean separation: apps/ services/ packages/ infra/
- Every service independently deployable
- Environment-agnostic (local Docker now, K8s later)
- No hardcoded ports or URLs anywhere — always from env


STACK — NEVER CHANGE:

Frontend (apps/web + apps/landing):
- React 18 + Vite + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS + Framer Motion
- Monaco Editor (@monaco-editor/react)
- Recharts + Cytoscape.js
- React Router v6
- Axios + React Query
- React Hot Toast
- Lucide React icons
- Socket.io client

Backend (services/api):
- Python 3.11
- FastAPI + Uvicorn
- SQLAlchemy 2.0 + Alembic
- Celery 5 + Redis
- Pydantic v2
- python-jose (JWT)
- passlib + bcrypt
- httpx + aiofiles
- ReportLab (PDF)
- SSLyze
- python-magic

Database:
- PostgreSQL 15

Cache + Queue:
- Redis 7

Reverse Proxy:
- Nginx (gateway)

Containers:
- Docker + docker-compose
- ZAP must have: platform: linux/amd64 (M2 fix)

AI / LLM:
Primary: OpenRouter API
Models in fallback order:
  1. qwen/qwen3-coder:free
  2. meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free
  3. nousresearch/hermes-3-llama-3.1-405b:free
  4. openai/gpt-oss-120b:free

Fallback: Groq API
Models:
  1. llama-3.3-70b-versatile
  2. qwen/qwen3-32b
  3. moonshotai/kimi-k2-instruct-0905

Future (plug in later, do not break existing):
- Google Gemini (Vertex AI)
- AWS Bedrock

ENV VARS NEEDED:
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
GROQ_API_KEY=
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@postgres:5432/shieldsentinel
REDIS_URL=redis://redis:6379/0
ZAP_URL=http://zap:8090
CELERY_BROKER_URL=redis://redis:6379/0
CELERY_RESULT_BACKEND=redis://redis:6379/1
JWT_SECRET=
JWT_ALGORITHM=HS256
JWT_EXPIRE_DAYS=7
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
UPLOAD_DIR=/tmp/shieldsentinel/uploads
REPORTS_DIR=/tmp/shieldsentinel/reports
ENVIRONMENT=development
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:4000



SECURITY TOOLS (installed in Docker):
DAST: OWASP ZAP, Nuclei, FFUF, Nikto, Wapiti
RECON: Nmap, theHarvester, Amass, Gobuster
INJECTION: SQLMap, XSStrike, Commix, NoSQLMap
SSL: SSLyze (Python), testssl.sh
SAST: Semgrep, Bandit, Gitleaks, TruffleHog, Trivy
STRESS: wrk, hey (HTTP load testing)
AUTH TESTING: jwt_tool
API TESTING: ZAP API mode, custom scripts

ATTACK PHILOSOPHY:
- Every scan: recon first, then attack, then verify
- Parameter extraction before injection (targeted not spray)
- Concurrent attack threads via Celery
- Rate limit testing on every endpoint
- Session abuse and token replay testing
- Input fuzzing on every discovered form field
- All attacks require user to confirm target ownership
- Results show: attacked / defended / not tested honestly




